==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Skimp
<hw>Skimp</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Skimped</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Skimping</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Cf. <er>Skinch</er>,
<er>Scamp</er>, <pos>v. t.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To slight; to
do carelessly; to scamp.</def> <mark>[Prov. Eng. & Colloq.
U.S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To make insufficient allowance for; to scant; to
scrimp.</def> <mark>[Prov. Eng. & Colloq. U. S.]</mark> <-- used with
"on"; to skimp on clothing so as to have enough food. -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Skimp</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Skimp
<hw>Skimp</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To save; to be parsimonious or
niggardly.</def> <mark>[Prov. Eng. & Colloq. U.S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Skimp</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Skimp
<hw>Skimp</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Scanty.</def> <mark>[Prov. Eng. &
Colloq. U.S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

